<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Military Official Ends Visit to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The chief of the General Staff of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army, General Fu Quanyou, today
ended his five-day visit to France.
</P>
<P>
Fu held talks on Monday with French Foreign Minister Herve de
Charette and the chief of staff of the French armed forces,
General Jean-Philippe Douin, to exchange views on developing
Sino-French political and military ties.
</P>
<P>
Fu and Douin also briefed each other on defense policies and
situation about the armed forces of their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
Fu also visited navy and air force bases in the Mediterranean
military region of the French armed forces, including a navy
training center, a frigate, an air force unit and an air piloting
school.
</P>
<P>
Fu arrived in France on Sunday for an official visit. 
</P>
