<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British National Science Week Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The fourth British National Week
of Science, Engineering and Technology, SET97, was launched by
Minister for Science and Technology Ian Taylor here today.
</P>
<P>
"Science week plays a major role in the campaign to improve the
nation's ability at appreciation of and interest in what will
continue to be the driving forces of economic and social change
for years to come," Taylor said.
</P>
<P>
Science week has been designed to promote a positive image of
science, engineering and technology and help show their value to
society.
</P>
<P>
It has also been designed to raise public awareness of science
and technology as a part of daily life.
</P>
<P>
"Engineers in particular have long been undervalued in this
country. For this reason, 1997 has been designated the Year of
Engineering Success (YES)," he said.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the YES campaign is to raise the profile of
engineering and encourage more young people to enter the
profession.
</P>
<P>
SET97 is organized by the British Association for the
Advancement of Science with near 6,000 events and runs from today
to March 23.
</P>
<P>
The first science week took place in 1994 with over 1,000
events across Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
