<HEADLINE> EU to Attend Middle East Talks in Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
today it had accepted the invitation from Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat to attend Saturday's meeting in Gaza on the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
It said in a statement that the EU will be represented at the
meeting by a local representative of The Netherlands, the rotating
EU presidency.
</P>
<P>
The peace process is "the only path" to security and peace for
the Palestinians as well as for Israel, the statement stressed.
</P>
<P>
While expressing concern over the lastest developments in the
peace process since the signing of Hebron agreement, the EU
pledged to help promote a just and lasting peace in the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
It said the EU will present "a number of European ideas and
options" to overcome the present difficulties and explore ways to
achieve further progress in the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks.
</P>
</TEXT>
