<HEADLINE> HK-Based Airlines Enhances Service to Bahrain, Dubai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong-based Cathay Pacific
Airways will add an additional flight to Bahrain and Dubai
beginning from March 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
William Ling, Cathay Pacific Route Manager for South East Asia
and Middle East, said that the new operating pattern offers
increased flexibility to passengers who can now choose to travel
from Hong Kong to Bahrain and Dubai non-stop in either direction.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesdays and Sundays, a flight will operate from Hong Kong
direct to Bahrain and onto Dubai, while on Thursdays and Fridays a
flight will maintain the existing pattern, flying from Hong Kong
direct to Dubai and onto Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
All flights will be operated by Boeing 777 aircraft.  
</P>
</TEXT>
