<HEADLINE> New Zealand, U.S. Lead in HK Women's Rugby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand and the Untied
States led their respective group standings after the opening-day
competitions at the inaugural Hong Kong Women's Rugby Sevens
Invitational Tournament here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand made a flying start in Group A with four
consecutive wins, beating Japan 26-5, Australia 29-0, England 26-0
and Canada 41-0. The Kiwis led the pool with 12 points, three
from each win.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand is expected to win over the Netherlands in its
final group match Sunday morning, thus qualifying for the Cup
Championship Sunday afternoon as Group A winners.
</P>
<P>
England followed with nine points from three wins Saturday to
rank second in the pool.
</P>
<P>
The United States of Group B were also unbeaten after the first
day, winning over Scotland 26-5, Hong Kong 10-7, Arabian Gulf 43-0
and Singapore 53-0. The Americans led the pool standings with 12
points.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Hong Kong scored three wins against one loss to rank
second in the group.
</P>
<P>
The top two teams of each group advance into the Cup
Championship, the third- and fourth-ranked sides enter the Plate
Championships and four other sides are to vie for the Bowl
Championship title.
</P>
<P>
All the semifinals and finals of the championships are set for
Sunday afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
