<HEADLINE> Mongolian PM: Government Measures Have Promoted Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian Prime Minister
Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan said today that the economy of his country
has improved as a result of the measures taken by his government
since it took power last July.
</P>
<P>
In an article carried in "Government News" today, Enkhsaikhan
said his government has raised energy prices since last September,
which has boosted the power sectors of the country. As a result,
coal output, electricity and heat production have all grown, he
added.
</P>
<P>
In response to workers' demand for higher pay, Enkhsaikhan
pointed out that wage increases may result in further growth in
inflation rate, which must be avoided. He said his government is
looking for a way which can increase workers' payment without
causing price rises.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in January and February was 2.3 percent and
3.2 percent respectively, lower than that of the same period of
last year, indicating that Mongolia's economy is moving towards
stabilization, the prime minister said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
