<HEADLINE> Khamenei: Iran to Continue Anti-U.S. Struggle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ali
Khamenei said today that Iran is determined to continue its
anti-U.S. struggle without any hesitation.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that Iran can not have any relations with the
United States because it is against Iran and its policy is based
on "oppression and tyranny."
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader made the remarks in a big gathering of the
Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) forces and volunteer
forces in the last day of his trip to Khuzestan province, where
an eight-year war from 1980 to 1988 between Iran and Iraq took
place.
</P>
<P>
"The United States would be the enemy of any country that
would stand in front of U.S. pursuit of illegitimate interests,"
he was quoted by the state-run Tehran Radio as saying.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the military forces in western Iran, Khamenei
called on them to have better understanding of their enemy and
follow the Islamic path with firmness and without "any fear."
</P>
<P>
He said "the U.S. support for Israel is not because of its
support for Jews but to meet its own interests."
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said last Sunday that Iran has struggled against the
United States for 18 years and it would continue this struggle
for 180 years.
</P>
<P>
However, President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani said recently that
Iran is pursuing a policy of no dialogue and no war toward the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Iran and the United States have been hostile to each other
for the past 18 years since they broke diplomatic relations in
1979 after the hostage crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
