<HEADLINE> PLC Working Group Drafts Rules of Procedure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The rules of procedure working
group under the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) has finished
the drafting of the rules of procedure for the legislative arm of
the future Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The Chinese version of the draft will be submitted to the PLC
plenary session, scheduled for next Saturday, for approval, said
Selina Chow, convenor of the sub-group, following a closed-door
meeting of her team in Shenzhen this morning.
</P>
<P>
Chow told a press briefing here that in accordance with the
relevant articles of the Basic Law and two related documents
endorsed by the Preparatory Committee for the HKSAR, the team
discussed the terms of reference of the PLC and its rules of
procedure.
</P>
<P>
The PLC will enact the laws indispensable to the HKSAR, as
empowered by the Preparatory Committee, and the laws will not go
into effect until July 1.
</P>
<P>
"Three Readings", a practice which is adopted by the current
Legislative Council, was included in the draft, as it has been
proved efficient in the normal operation of a legislature, Chow
noted.
</P>
<P>
She continued to point out that the draft was finished in a
very short time. "We must have the rules of procedure ready to be
used as soon as possible," she noted.
</P>
<P>
Two working groups were set up at the PLC's plenary session in
February, one on administrative matters and the other on rules of
procedure, each having 12 members.
</P>
<P>
Then the panels had closed-door meetings respectively in
Shenzhen on weekends.  
</P>
</TEXT>
