<HEADLINE> New Anti-drug Act Passed in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- President Joaquim Chissano
endorsed a new anti-drug act today to replace the old one in the
colonial era, which deals stricter with drug smugglers.
</P>
<P>
During debate at sessions of the Republican Assembly before
the act comes into effect, some parliamentary members opposed to
considering cannabis as drug, saying farmers here plant and use
it on a widespread basis.
</P>
<P>
But most of the mps favored treating cannabis as other drugs.
</P>
<P>
The new act stipulates that those who plant, produce, sell and
distribute cannabis will be sentenced for 16-20 years of
imprisonment. And those who illegally distribute or smuggle drugs
will be sent to the prison for as long as 30 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
