<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0058 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Fetches 24 Million US Dollars on Tea Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's tea production totaled
37.081 million kilograms (kg) and export stood at 19.578 million
kg in the first seven months of the current fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The tea production was 1.072 million kg more in seven months
upto January than the corresponding period of the last fiscal
year, according to the monthly statistical bulletin of the
Bangladesh Tea Board received here today.
</P>
<P>
The production target has been fixed at 54 million kg for the
fiscal 1996-97 starting from July 1, 1996 to June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin also said Bangladesh had earned 24.24 million
dollars by exporting 19.578 million kg loose and packet tea upto
January this year compared to 19.5 million dollars by exporting
14.336 million kg in the same period of the last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The regular buyer Poland has so far imported the highest
quantity of tea from Bangladesh (6.017 million kg), followed by
Pakistan (4.457 million kg) and Afghanistan (3.595 million kg)
upto January.
</P>
<P>
Among the new tea importers, China bought 1.247 million kg, Sri
Lanka 37,000 kg, Ukraine 22,000 kg and Kuwait 9,000 kg upto the
month, the bulletin added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
