<HEADLINE> HK to Open Tourist Office in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Tourist
Association is to open an office in Beijing later this month,
which will be its first in China's mainland.
</P>
<P>
The mainland is already the second biggest source of visitors
to Hong Kong after Japan, according to today's South China Morning
Post.
</P>
<P>
The association's Peter Randall was quoted as saying Hong
Kong's tourist agencies already have close relations with both
national and regional tourist bodies in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
"We see in the future our cooperation expanding to other
parts. An office in the capital will be useful," he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Hong Kong was visited by more than 2.3 million
visitors from the mainland, or 19.7 percent of territory's tourist
arrivals in the year. 
</P>
