<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Border Between Yugoslavia, Albania Closed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav Supreme Defense
Committee has decided to close the border between Yugoslavia and
Albania and ordered its border-keeping forces to be on the red
alert, a military spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Novinska Agencija Tanjug, the spokesman of the
office of the General Staff of the Yugoslav Army said the Yugoslav
government is taking precautionary measures to avoid possible
negative impacts from the deteriorating situation in Albania on
the national security of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Though the chaos in Albania has not posed direct threat to
Yugoslavia so far and the situation at the border areas remains
calm, there exist possibilities of border conflicts if the
situation in Albania worsens, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Firstly, the government feared that a large number of Albanian
refugees might swarm into Yugoslavia with arms and ammunitions, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, the government feared that some Albanian extremists
living in Kosovo bordering Albania might be encouraged to snatch
weapons from local army and police for terrorist attacks, he added.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to avoid any possible bad results, the Yugoslav
border-keeping forces and the navy have coordinated with each
other in patrolling, he said, adding that a security zone has been
set up in the districts bordering Albania.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav special forces and the Air Force were also on a
alert, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
