<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 killed in Mine Explosion in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Two civilians were killed and
eight others wounded today in a mine explosion in the Jaffna
district in Northern province of Sri Lanka, according to a
military spokesman here.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that rebels of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have activated a claymore mine at a civil bus
which was proceeding from Talaiady to Jaffna city this morning.
</P>
<P>
Two civilians were killed and at least eight others injured due
to the explosion and the injured were evacuated to Pallai hospital
in the Jaffna peninsula, he added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a guerrilla war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
island country since 1983.  
</P>
</TEXT>
