</P>
<P>
-- British Prime Minister John Major will launch the
Conservative general election campaign today with an attempt to
reclaim the center ground from Labor party leader Tony Blair and a
promise that the next Tory government will help the "have-nots
become the haves."
</P>
<P>
The Financial Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The United Kingdom will block what it sees as a European
Union conspiracy to undermine British beef sales by insisting that
all beef be labelled with its place of origin.
</P>
<P>
