<HEADLINE> Albanian Rebels Occupy Border Areas With Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Rebels in Albania have occupied
areas bordering the Republic of Macedonia and looted all the posts
previously controlled by the Albanian border guards, Novinska
Agencija Tanjug reported today.
</P>
<P>
Tanjug quoted some witnesses as saying that there is not a
single Albanian border guard at the posts now.
</P>
<P>
Villagers living in the areas snatched away not only the
weapons deserted by border guards, but also furnitures, equipment
and even doors as well as windows.
</P>
<P>
Residents from the border areas on the Macedonia's side said
that they heard non-stop gunshots coming from Albania for 30 hours.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian Defense Minister Blagoj Handziski visited the border
areas on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the commands issued by Macedonian President Kiro
Gligorov and the General Staff of the Macedonian Army, the
Macedonian border troops have been on the red alert.
</P>
<P>
Albania has been in chaos after nationwide protests turned into
street violence recently, which quickly spread from the south to
other areas of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
