<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Laos Hits 6.7 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Contractual foreign investment in
Laos has already reached 6.7 billion U.S. dollars since the
country adopted the policy of reforms and opening to the outside
world in 1986, according to official statistics from Vientiane
today.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment in Laos has been increasing steadly over the
past 10 years. Since 1986, particularly since early 1994 when
land-locked Laos enacted a law to simplify procedures for foreign
businesses, investors from more than 30 countries and regions have
put in money in 616 projects, mainly in the sectors of mine
exploration, tourism, transportation, tele-communication,
electronics, manufacture and handcraft.
</P>
<P>
Among countries with the largest amounts of investments in Laos
are the United States, France, Australia, China, South Korea,
Malaysia and Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
