<HEADLINE> Turkey to Buy Missiles from France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Turkey has decided to buy
middle-range IHAWK missiles from the French Ground Forces through
French firm Thomson-CFS, local newspaper Daily News reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that under the deal, eight IHAWK batteries will
be delivered to Turkey from France's surplus arms.
</P>
<P>
The decision for the purchase of the missiles was made during
the Turkish and French defense industries cooperation meeting
held last month in Paris following an announcement from the
Belgium Defense Ministry to freeze its plans to sell the IHAWK
missiles, known as surface-to-air missiles.
</P>
<P>
The IHAWK missiles are manufactured by U.S. firm Raytheon.
</P>
<P>
The Belgium Defense Ministry earlier confirmed that
negotiations were continuing over the sale of the IHAWK missiles
to Turkey, but later the ministry canceled its plans.
</P>
