<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Arrested for Cultivating Marijuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian Drug Enforcement
Commission (DEC) has arrested a farmer in Kalomo district,
Southern Province for cultivation and unlawfully possession of
3.56 tons of marijuana worth about 685,000 U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The local press today quoted DEC spokesman Mukutulu Sinyani as
confirming the arrest that the 47-year-old farmer was detained at
his home where he had stored the narcotic drug.
</P>
<P>
No further details were given by the press.
</P>
<P>
The DEC has set into motion a cannabis eradication strategy in
the country's Southern Province after an upswing in the growing
of the drug in that area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
