<HEADLINE> Slovenia's Tourism Income Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Tourism income of the Republic
of Slovenia in 1996 reached 1.22 billion U.S. dollars, a 13
percent increase over that of 1.08 billion dollars in 1995, said a
report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The statistics, disclosed by the tourism commission of the
Slovenian Economic Association, said that up to 831,400 foreign
tourists visited the country in the year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign tourists in January this year increased by 13 percent
as compared with the same period last year, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Slovenian tourism authorities estimated that tourism
earnings in 1997 will amount to 1.45 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
