<HEADLINE> Resolution Honors Richard Jewell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Richard Jewell, the former
security guard and onetime suspect in the Atlanta Centennial
Olympic Park bombing, was honored for spotting the bomb and
helping clear the park before the explosion.
</P>
<P>
A resolution adopted by the state Senate Friday honored both
Jewell and Georgia Bureau of Investigation agent Tom Davis.
</P>
<P>
Davis telephoned the bomb squad and helped evacuate the park on
July 27 after Jewell told him he saw a suspicious backpack.
</P>
<P>
A similar resolution praising Jewell was passed by the state
House in January.
</P>
<P>
Jewell, initially hailed as a hero, was named as a suspect in
news accounts three days later. Three months later, the FBI
exonerated him.
</P>
<P>
One person died and 111 were injured in the accident.
</P>
<P>
The bombing case is still under investigation, no arrests
having been made yet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
