<HEADLINE> Quarry Buries 7 People In N. Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven People were buried
alive after a quarry at Moivaro village in Arumeru District of
Arusha Region, northern Tanzania collapsed amid strong winds.
</P>
<P>
The local press today quoted the Arumeru District Executive
Officer (DEO) Mrs. Bernadetta Kinabo as saying that the incident
occurred on Thursday evening when the deceased were loading a
lorry with gravel.
</P>
<P>
Five bodies have already been recovered and exhumed.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Kinabo said two other bodies were yet to be exhumed,
adding that rescue operations were still going on.
</P>
<P>
She noted the lorry into which they were loading the gravel
belonged to the Anti-poaching Squad, explaining that the driver
and a person escaped unhurt.
</P>
<P>
The DEO admitted that it was environmental degradation to the
area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
