<HEADLINE> Austria, Hungary to Further Boost Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Federal Chancellor
Viktor Klima today concluded his one-day visit to Hungary after
talks on further strengthening bilateral relations with his
Hungarian counterpart Horn Gyula.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after the talks, the two leaders
said they exchanged views on the ways to ease the bottleneck
conditions and combat crimes at the border crossing between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Klima said that Austria, a member state of the European Union
(EU), backs Hungary's bid to join the international organization.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders agreed that cooperation among Austria, Hungary
and Slovakia should be boosted, which will help Hungary and
Slovakia to meet on time the economic criteria set by the
Maastricht Treaty to be eligible for EU membership.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian President Goncz Arpad and President of the National
Assembly Gal Zoltan also held separate talks with Klima. 
</P>
</TEXT>
