<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Reports Slight Growth in National Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Russia said today that its economy
grew slightly in January and February as a result of the nation's
desperate efforts to reverse the downward trend of economy over
the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the National Statistics Committee indicated the
January-February gross domestic product (GDP) in the country grew
by 0.5 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output value increased 0.9 percent and retail sales
of commodities two percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, major social indexes in Russia were also slightly
improved, the data shows.
</P>
<P>
Employees' income in the period increased five percent over the
same months last year, while the number of people who earned less
than the minimum cost of living dropped by 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
The speed of price rise also slowed down. In January, the index
of price growth hit 102.3 percent and the next month fell to 101.5
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
