<HEADLINE> Renowned Climber to Make His 11th Qomolangma Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Nepalese mountaineer who
has reached the top of the world for ten times, is to make his
11th attempt to conquer the 8,848-meter Mt. Qomolangma in this
spring climbing season, local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Ang Rita Sherpa, a 49-year-old owner of a Kathmandu travel
agency, this time will guide a Russian expedition to adventure an
unexplored route of the north face of the mountain on the Chinese
side.
</P>
<P>
The Russian climbing team, which has arrived here from Russia's
Republic of North Osetia, is scheduled to leave Kathmandu Monday
and make the ascent probably in late April or early May.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Qomolangma, or Sagarmatha in Nepalese, lies on the border
between Nepal and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
