<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Diplomats Evacuated From Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Most Yugoslav diplomats in the
Albanian capital Tirana were evacuated on Friday, leaving only two
behind for emergency contact.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministry said today that the Yugoslavians were
evacuated from Tirana along with diplomats from other western
countries by helicopters provided by the multi-national stability
force SFOR stationed in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
With the agreement of the Yugoslav government, six German
helicopters got 120 diplomats, including those from Germany,
Norway, Denmark, Switzerland, Japan, Poland, Bosnia, Hungary and
other countries, out of Albania to Germany.
</P>
<P>
The helicopters were fired on as they took off from the Tirana
airport, but there were no casualties.
</P>
<P>
European countries and the United States began to evacuate
foreign nationals from crisis-hit Albania on Thursday as the
unrest which has gripped the country since January made it too
dangerous for foreigners to stay there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
