<HEADLINE> Afforestation Going Smoothly In Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang province
has finished 77 percent of its afforestation quota for this year.
</P>
<P>
Statististics show that 30,000 ha of trees have been
planted. Playing a key role in the comprehensive development
process in the mountainous areas in the province, cash trees and
bamboo have covered 80 percent of the afforestation area.
</P>
<P>
The province, with fast economic development, paid close
attention to the improvement of environment by afforestation in
the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The provincial forest bureau sent five teams to 11 cities and
prefectures to check afforestation efforts. Besides, local
governments also provided tree seedlings, chemical fertilizers and
techniques to guide the tree planting drive.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the afforestation project using World Bank
loans for planting 13,000 ha of trees in the province is going on
with speed with 80 percent having been completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
