<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 9th SAARC Summit to Open in Male on May 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The ninth summit of the South
Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) will begin on
May 12 in Male, capital of the Maldives, according to Sri Lankan
Foreign Ministry sources today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said attending the three-day summit will be heads
of state of the seven member countries -- India, Bangladesh,
Pakistan, Nepal, Bhutan, the Maldives and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
On the summit agenda will be a South Asian Free Trade Area,
South Asian Preferential Trade Arrangement, the elimination of
regional plagues such as drug trafficking, cross-border terrorism,
child abuse and smuggling, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The draft agenda will be circulated among member countries
before its adoption, said the sources, adding that preliminary
talks will start on May 5 with an SAARC Foreign Secretaries
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
