<HEADLINE> Power Supply to East China Guaranteed: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Electric
Power Shi Dazhen pledged that power supply for economic
development of Shanghai and other areas of east China would be
guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
This pledge was made at a recent national meeting on power
industry held in Shanghai, attended by leading local officials in
charge of power industry from all over the country.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the meeting disclose that this year, the east
China power grid will provide 212 billion kw/hours of electricity,
which is believed to be able to generally meet the power demand
for national economic construction and development in Shanghai
Municipality, and Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Anhui provinces.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, power industrial authorities have also decided
to continue to build more power plants on the Yangtze River and
along the coast -- with Anhui constructing more thermal power
plants, Zhejiang building more hydropower stations and continuing
the construction of Qinshan Nuclear Power Plant, Jiangsu being
authorized to build one new nuclear power station in Lianyungang
city, Pudong New Area of Shanghai constructing thermal power
plants.
</P>
<P>
They have also pledged to make greater efforts to transmit more
electricity from energy-strong provinces of west China to east
China and to speed the construction of gas-burning power stations
in east China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
