<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Funds Play Important Role in Fujian's Urban Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment has become an
important force in advancing urban construction in east China
coastal province of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Information from the local urban construction bureau shows that
overseas funds account for a half of the province's total
investment put for urban construction, rebuilding of old city
areas and development of large tracts of land.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors have invested 2.15 billion U.S. dollars in
1,332 projects.
</P>
<P>
The province has reconstructed 1,300 hectares of old city
districts, and has built flats with a combined floor space of 20
million sq m, repaired and widened more than 500 km of roads and
built 128 bridges with the aid of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
Observers here also say that the inflow of overseas funds has
not only alleviate the province's financial shortage for urban
construction, but also brought in advanced concepts on management,
decoration and engineering in the province's real estate sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
