<HEADLINE> 7 Killed, 15 Injured in Bomb Blast in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 15 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
killed and about 15 injured in a bomb blast in Pakistan's eastern
Punjab Province, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The bomb went off at 1:05 p.m. (0735 GMT) Friday in a car park
outside the main railway station in the eastern Punjab city of
Jullundhar, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Police said there were heavy casualties because the station was
crowded at that time.
</P>
<P>
The Punjab police have blamed a militant group for the blast.
</P>
