<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Journalist Killed in Kiev </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A journalist working for one of
Ukraine's most popular newspapers, Kiev Dispatches, was found
hanged in a deserted boiler room in a building outside Kiev today.
</P>
<P>
Police said there were no external injuries on the body of
Peter Shevchenko and they don't know if his death was murder or
suicide.
</P>
<P>
Shevchenko's colleagues on the paper, which has a daily
circulation of 250,000, said he was not the sort of person who
would kill himself.
</P>
<P>
The journalist, stationed in the city of Lugnansk, had been in
Kiev on Wednesday on a business trip.
</P>
<P>
He made a name for himself after writing a series of articles
about conflicts between the Lugansk Mayor Alexei Daninoy and the
regional security bureau.
</P>
<P>
Before Shevchenko's death, the Kiev Dispatches had been
carrying allegations about the mayor's wife using government money
for personal purposes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
