<HEADLINE> Nanchang Simplifies Approval Procedures For Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Nanchang, capital of east
China's Jiangxi province, has set a new rule to simplify the
approval procedures for foreign invesment.
</P>
<P>
Since this week, foreign investors wishing to invest in the
city will wait for no more than six days to get the approval. The
deadline of approval procedures for construction projects will be
also cut to 15 days.
</P>
<P>
The city will open wider to the outside world, using the
opportunity of the operation of the Beijing-Kowloon Railway, said
a local official.
</P>
<P>
He said that the city has set up centers in charge of foreign
investment and handling foreign complaints. A fee-charging center
was also built to prevent illegal fees from being imposed on
foreign-funded firms.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 1,500 foreign-funded firms have been set up
in the city, involving a combined foreign funding of 1.28 billion
US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
