<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Hold Technology Fairs Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the leading
manufacturing center in China, will hold technology fairs in
Malaysia and Australia from March 19-22 and March 27-28,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The two fairs, jointly sponsored by the municipal science and
technology commission, and the foreign trade and economic
cooperation commission, are aimed at promoting technical
cooperation between Shanghai and overseas countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the municipal government, more than 100 scientific
research institutes, universities, firms and foreign trade
organizations from Shanghai will exhibit some 500 high and new
technologies, practical techniques and their products at the fairs.
</P>
<P>
Most of the technologies, covering ten sectors such as
machinery and electronics, chemicals, and textiles, will be shown
for the first time and some of them are of advanced standards in
the world.  
</P>
