<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Calls for Calm in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian Foreign Ministry today
called for the return of stability in crisis-hit Albania through
democratic channels and political dialogue.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the ministry said Ukraine is very concerned
about the situation in Albania which is on the verge of civil war
as gun-toting rebels fight in the streets in protest against
President Sali Berisha.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministry statement said that the Ukrainian
government believes that it is necessary to avoid any further
military force in solving the internal crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine hopes Albania, a member of the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and the Council of
Europea, can solve its internal problems under Albania's existing
laws and through its commitment to international obligations.
</P>
<P>
The statement also urged the international community, primarily
the OSCE and European Union, to help Albania to emerge from the
crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
