<HEADLINE> Albanian Ministers Call for Reconciliation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Albania's Defense Minister Shakir
Vukaj and Interior Minister Belul Cela on Friday appealed for calm
and called on Albanians to begin reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
"The motherland is superior to everything," said Vukaj. He
called on individuals and mass organizations throughout the
country to cooperate with each other and restore stability to the
country.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister also called on people to hand in the
weapons they are holding and stop attacking arsenals and military
camps.
</P>
<P>
Vukaj warned, "Any action against ethnic groups and against the
country will be punished."
</P>
<P>
Albania has been in the grip of unrest since January after the
collapse of pyramid investment schemes in which thousands of
Albanians lost their life savings.
</P>
<P>
The protests turned violent two weeks ago as rebels looted
weapons from army depots and started fighting the military.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Bashkim Fino on Friday asked the European Union
to provide military and humanitarian assistance to restore order
in the Balkan country which is on the verge of civil war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
