<HEADLINE> 1.6 Tons of Illegal Drugs Burned in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1.6 tons of illegal
drugs, were burned today in the state of Rio Grande Do Sul in
southern Brazil, the largest quantity of drugs confiscated in the
state this year, Brazilian authorities announced.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, worth 7.5 million U.S. dollars, were burned in the
furnaces of the Riograndense Steel Company in Porto Alegre, the
capital of Rio Grande Do Sul.
</P>
<P>
The haul included 1.5 tons of marijuana and 100 kilos of
cocaine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
