<HEADLINE> French President Ends Visit to Uruguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques
Chirac left for Bolivia today at the end of his 20-hour visit to
Uruguay, the second leg of his eight-day tour of Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the visit was to reinforce the presence of
France and the European Union (EU) in Latin America, especially in
the four-nation Southern Common Market (Mercosur) trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
Chirac and his Uruguayan counterpart Julio Maria Sanguinetti
had a private meeting during the visit.
</P>
<P>
Both presidents stressed the importance of relations between
the EU and Latin America, especially with Mercosur, and committed
themselves to further strengthen ties between the two regional
blocs.
</P>
<P>
Chirac proposed a summit meeting of European and Latin American
presidents to promote the rapprochement of the two continents. The
Uruguayan president expressed his full support for the proposal.
</P>
<P>
Several agreements were signed during the visit, including an
accord to stimulate contacts between the private sector to improve
technological development and competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The French president, who was presented with the Medal of the
Republic, also laid the foundation stone for the new French
Embassy and inaugurated the first Renault automobile plant in
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
