<HEADLINE> U.S. Albania Airlift Mission Halted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States has suspended
its airlift evacuation of Americans from crisis-hit Albania after
a Marine helicopter was fired on by a missile from the ground.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter returned fire, but no casualties were reported
on either side.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. began evacuating some 2000 Americans from Albania on
Thursday after the violence which has gripped the country for the
last two weeks spread to the capital Tirana.
</P>
<P>
The evacuation mission had taken 408 Americans to safety before
the reported missile attack, which caused the suspension of the
airlift effort.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an Italian military helicopter carrying out its
evacuation mission was also attacked by light weapons from the
ground, with no casualties reported.
</P>
<P>
Albania has slipped deeper and deeper into chaos since the
unrest triggered by the collapse of pyramid investment schemes in
which thousands of Albanians lost their life savings turned
violent two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Rebels looted weapons from army depots and used them to fight
the military. Several cities in southern Albania are now
controlled by rebels who have now entered capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
