<HEADLINE> 65 Rebels Killed, 30 Bases Destroyed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-five Tamil rebels were
killed and nearly 30 rebel bases destroyed in the Mullaitivu
jungles and along the eastern sea coast of Sri Lanka during
Thursday's combined operation by government forces.
</P>
<P>
The operation was a combined attack launched Thursday morning
by the Army, Air Force and Navy with gunboats, aircraft and
artillery simultaneously pounding rebel positions in the
Mullaitivu district, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the attacks were centered mainly on the
rebels' so-called 14 base complexes in the Mullaitivu jungles.
</P>
<P>
The reports added that Tamil rebels' transmissions monitored by
government troops indicated that the military had taken the
"enemy" who had suffered heavily, completely by surprise.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war against the
Sri Lankan government for a separate Tamil state in the north and
east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
</TEXT>
