<HEADLINE> Jenson Beats Eyles in Austrian Squash Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Dan Jenson of Australia defeated
compatriot and second seed Rodney Eyles 15-10, 7-15, 11-15, 15-10,
17-15 to book a final date with top seed Jansher Khan of Pakistan
at the Austrian Open squash tournament in Linz, Austria on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Khan had to battle from two sets down in his semi-final clash
with Julien Bonetat of France before triumphing 14-15, 13-15,
15-4, 15-10, 15-9 after a fascinating 81-minute struggle.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event, top-seeded Australian Narelle Tippett
ousted eighth seed Stephanie Brind of England 9-3, 9-4, 10-8 to
reach a final showdown with compatriot and fifth seed Kate Major,
who defeated her twin sister Emma, seeded seven, 9-6, 8-10, 9-0,
5-9, 9-2 in 75 minutes. 
