<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Xingye Bank Eyes Shanghai Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Fujian Xingye Bank (FXB),
which is now building a 33-story office compound in the Bund area
of Shanghai, has worked hard to enter the local financial market
in China's largest city.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Xingye became the first Chinese bank from outside
Shanghai to settle in the city by opening a local branch, which
has been expanding rapidly ever since.
</P>
<P>
According to Gao Jianping, director of the FXB branch, his bank
will offer a series of new services, including newly-approved
foreign exchange businesses and supplying buyer's credits to
enterprises from Shanghai and Fujian province.
</P>
<P>
The FXB Shanghai branch, which was started with a capital of
100 million yuan and five million US dollars, collected 1.32
billion yuan in deposits, two billion yuan in total assets and 33
million yuan in profits by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, the branch has increased its
assets to as much as three billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The FXB Shanghai Branch has boosted the exchange and
cooperation in economic and financial fields between Shanghai and
Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Gao said that the branch has been part of the city's banking
sector and plans to become a regional banking institution based in
Shanghai and serving the whole Yangtze River Delta region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
