<HEADLINE> Albanian Parliament Trusts Fino Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian parliament tonight
gave a vote of confidence in the new all-party reconciliation
government led by Prime Minister Bashkim Fino by passing an
administrative program proposed by the new premier.
</P>
<P>
Fino listed the resumption of order and social stability,
economic stability, guaranteeing food supplies, and controlling
the country's finances as the four most important tasks the
government faces.
</P>
<P>
Fino also promised to prepare for parliamentary elections by
the end of June.
</P>
<P>
Albania has been in the grip of unrest since January after the
collapse of pyramid investment schemes in which thousands of
Albanians lost their life savings.
</P>
<P>
The protests turned violent two weeks ago after rebels looted
weapons from army depots and started fighting. Several cities in
southern Albania are now controlled by rebels and the armed
conflict has now moved to the north of the country and the capital
Tirana.
</P>
<P>
Unrest has been growing in Tirana itself. Mobs looted a
warehouse of 650 tons of flour on Thursday and raided security
force depots in search of guns.
</P>
<P>
Albanian President Sali Berisha Thursday decided to deploy
tanks in front of the main institutions in the country and called
for foreign military intervention to halt the disorder. 
</P>
