<HEADLINE> Beijing Boasts Numerous Cultural Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A recent general survey shows
that China's capital abounds in cultural relics, said an official
with the Beijing Bureau of Cultural Relics.
</P>
<P>
Beijing boasts more than 7,000 ancient sites, including 42
state-level protection areas, 223 at the city protection level and
700 at the county protection level.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, the United Nations Educational, Scientific and
Cultural Organization (UNESCO) approved the Great Wall, the
Imperial Palace and a site of ancient inhabitants in Beijing onto
the World Heritage List.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile many old-style lanes, guild halls, theaters, old
shops and compounds with houses around a square courtyard have
been preserved by the municipal government. 
</P>
