<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Invests in Zhangzhou's Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan businessmen and companies
have offered funding for 285 agricultural firms in the city of
Zhangzhou, in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The firms, involving a combined investment of more than 300
million US dollars, exported 140 million US dollars-worth of
products in 1996 alone.
</P>
<P>
It has been a priority of the local government to attract
overseas funds to develop agriculture, a pillar industry for
Zhangzhou. More preferential policies will be issued to support
expansion of the agricultural sector, local authorities say.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou used foreign funds to develop crop planting, animal
breeding and processing of agricultural and sideline products, and
agricultural management, they say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
