<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru's Tourism Income Soars in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Peru's earnings from tourism rose 39
percent last year to 725 million U.S. dollars, the Industry and
Tourism Ministry announced today.
</P>
<P>
Each tourist spent an average of 1,142 dollars in the country,
a rise of 16.3 percent over 1995's 980 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists visiting Peru has trebled over the last
four years. In 1996, 668,500 people visited the country, up from
216,534 in 1992.
</P>
<P>
That's brought about a three fold rise in foreign currency
earnings. In 1992, tourism in Peru earned 188 million dollars,
rising by 42 percent in 1993, 50 percent in 1994 and 29 percent in
1995 to 520 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
