<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Ensures Two Golds at All England Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese players ensured two
titles inthe men's and women's singles at the All-England
Badminton Championships after the semi-finals here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the men'ss singles, China's Sun Jun beat Indonisia's
Heryanto Arbi 15-10, 15-11, while Sun's teammate Dong Jiong
outplayed Olympic champion Denmark's Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen 15-8,
15-10.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, world number one and top seed Gong
Zhichao from China crushed Ra Kyung-min of South Korea with 11-2,
11-2. The 19-year old Gong beat Indonisia's Susi Susanti on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Last year's All England women's doubles champions Ge Fei and Gu
Jun from China beat Denmark's Helene Kirkegaard and Rikke Olsen
Friday evening at Birmingham's National Indoor Arena 15-3, 15-6.
They will meet Indonisia's Eliza and Resiana Zelin, who beat
China's Liu Zhong and Huang Nanyan at 15-12, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
In the mixed doubles, China's Liu Yong and Ge Fei beat England
Chris Hunt and Donna Kellogg 15-6, 15-4, setting up a final clash
against Indonisia's trikus Heryanto and Minarti Timur.
</P>
<P>
In men's doubles, Dannish Holst-Christensen and Michael Sogaard
beat Malaysia's Cheah Soon Kit and Yap Kim Hock 15-8, 12-15 and
15-11. The other winners of men's double semifinal are Ha
Tae-Kwon and Kang Kyung Jin from South Korea who beat Indonisia's
Sigit and Chandra Wijaya 15-11 and 15-7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
