<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Protects Farmland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The protected area of farmland
in central China's Henan Province, a major grain producer in the
country, has so far reached 7.3 million ha.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that this illustrates the province's success in
saving farmland from being overtaken for other uses.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, the craze for building development zones
claimed a significant amount of farmland. The grain-growing area
also decreased as a result of the development of sideline
production in rural areas such as aquiculture and fruit
cultivation.
</P>
<P>
To curb the trend, the local government in 1994 worked out a
regulation to protect farmland, which strictly safeguarded the
production bases for grain, cotton, oil-bearing crops and
vegetables.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the provincial government further strengthened its
management of farmland and reclaimed the right to approve the use
of land which had been transferred to lower-level governments.
</P>
<P>
It also launched a series of checks on idle farmland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
