<HEADLINE> Cyprus Police Identify Srrested US Basketball Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Police in Cyprus on Friday
identified five Americans, including four professional basketball
players, who were arrested for allegedly beating up an off-duty
Cypriot policeman.
</P>
<P>
The five allegedly attacked anti-terrorist squad policeman
Christodoulos Christodoulou in the early hours of Thursday at a
restaurant in a Nicosia suburb, police said.
</P>
<P>
A fight broke out after Christodoulou asked the Americans to
stop insulting his date. A number of other customers in the
restaurant became involved in the brawl and police were called to
the scene.
</P>
<P>
The Americans were arrested and remanded in custody for five
days by a Nicosia district court on charges of causing grievous
bodily harm.
</P>
<P>
They were identified as Randy Davis, 25, Kip Stone, 25, Michael
Reese, 27, and Reed Anthony, 26, who all play basketball for local
first division teams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
