<HEADLINE> Albanian Former Defence Minister Flees to Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Albania's former Defence Minister
Safet Zhulali had fled to Italy to escape the serious crisis in
the country, the local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The two kids of President Sali Berisha had also fled to Italy,
it was reported.
</P>
<P>
Albania has been in the grip of unrest since January after the
collapse of pyramid investment schemes in which thousands of
Albanians lost their life savings.
</P>
<P>
The protests turned violent two weeks ago as rebels looted
weapons from army depots and started fighting the
military. Several cities in southern Albania are in the hands of
rebels who are now threatening to move onto the capital.
</P>
<P>
Albanian President Sali Berisha and all political parties have
allegedly called on the Western European Union to provide military
assistance to Tirana to restore order in the country which is
verging on civil war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
