<HEADLINE> Jalabert Extends Leads in Paris-Nice Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- World number two Laurent Jalabert
of France extended his overall lead after taking the sixth stage
in the Paris-Nice cycling race on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert made his move as the peloton ascended Mont-Ventoux,
the toughest climb of the 182km stage, to see off Swiss Laurent
Dufaux and Spaniards Santiago Blanco and Mikel Zarrabeitia in a
sprint finish.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert escaped with some 90 kilometers to go with the help of
his ONCE teammates to boost his overall advantage over Dufaux to
46 seconds with two days remaining. 
