<BODY>
<HEADLINE> MLS to Make Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Major League Soccer will make
expansion for the 1998 season, adding teams in Miami and Chicago.
</P>
<P>
The new clubs would bring the league, which began last year, to
12 teams.
</P>
<P>
An official announcement from MLS officials is expected by
mid-April.
</P>
<P>
Miami would continue the MLS strategy of marketing to the
growing Latino sports fan base. Chicago also has a broad ethnic
mix in its population.
</P>
<P>
Both will enhance the league's image for television
negotiations after the 1998 season.
</P>
<P>
The league, which exceeded attendance expectations last year in
its first season, had planned to expand in 1999.
</P>
<P>
A complicating factor for new and established MLS clubs will be
the 1998 World Cup. Training and matches will occupy much of the
MLS season and no break is planned to accomodate the finals in
France, so many stars are likely to be absent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
