<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Liaises With NATO, OSCE on Action in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
today it was working closely with the Organization for Security
and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and NATO on a coordinated urgent
response to the deepening crisis in Albania.
</P>
<P>
"The union is coordinating closely with the OSCE and will
liaise actively with NATO and other organizations, so that
appropriate action can be taken urgently," the EU said in a
statement released by the Dutch Presidency.
</P>
<P>
"The European Union expresses grave concern at the breakdown of
civil order in Albania," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"It calls upon the government, political forces and other
groups throughout the country to refrain from violence and to work
for the restoration of order and a return to a proper democratic
process, which is the only way to overcome the present crisis," it
added.
</P>
<P>
The EU reiterated its support for OSCE mediator Franz Vranitzky
who was meeting Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino today as part
of international efforts to halt more than a month of political
violence.
</P>
<P>
"The union expects that the safety of foreign nationals will be
safeguarded at all times," the EU statement added.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government Thursday called for military
intervention by the Western European Union, NATO's European club,
to halt spreading disorder as the Western nations evacuated
nationals from the countries.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the European Union are expected to
discuss, among other things, the bloc's strategy towards the
current crisis in Albania at their semi-annually informal meeting
during the weekend in Apeldoorn, the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
