<HEADLINE> Iranian President Condemns Jewish Settlements in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today condemned the Jewish settlement construction in
East Jerusalem and called U.S. support for Israel as "callow and
oppressive."
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani made the statement in a large gathering at the
Shrine of late Iranian spiritual leader Ruhollah Mousavi
Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
He said that the "extreme callow and oppressive" stance of the
U.S. at the U.N. Security Council session was really a disgrace
for the United States.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said the issue had been raised in the U.N. Security
Council and all the member countries, except the U.S., voted
against Israel. However, it was the United States which cruelly
vetoed the draft resolution.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, the issue was raised at the U.N. General
Assembly session on Thursday and all the countries, except the
U.S. and Israel, voted against it.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president said that these affairs were among
important contemporary issues, which needed to be recorded in
the history and surveyed.
</P>
<P>
"Such an issue should serve as a warning and a
lesson to be learned by other nations, including Muslim
countries," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"We are surprised to see our brothers in Arab countries
calling the United States as their own friends," Rafsanjani was
quoted by the official news agency IRNA as saying,
</P>
<P>
He said: "At the time when the United States is fully
dependent on the Persian gulf littoral Arab states and other
Muslim countries today, it has shamelessly stood against them and
denied Palestinian Muslims' legitimate rights."
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said that he had warned the Muslim world that
Israelis were planing to build new Jewish settlements in both
East and West of Jerusalem in order to usurp those areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
