<HEADLINE> Greek Navy Conducts Evacuation Mission in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Greek navy's torpedo boat
Kavaloudis evacuated 44 Greek citizens and a number of foreign
nationals from the Albanian port of Durres this afternoon, the
Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
As Kavaloudis left, the frigate Aegaio moved in to pick up more
Greek and foreign civilians to take them to the Greek island of
Corfu. The operation is being backed up by another torpedo boat, a
minesweeper and a team of divers.
</P>
<P>
