<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Plane Crash Kills 86 in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A total of 86 passengers and crew
members were killed in an Iranian military plane crash near
Neyshabur city, about 700 kilometers northeast of Tehran, on
Thursday night, local media said here today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the C-130
plane of Iranian armed forces crashed over the Mashhad-Neyshabour
heights at 18:00 local time (14:30 GMT) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An airlines spokesman said that the crash left no
survivors. The victims were either military personnel or their
families.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that eight of the victims belonged to
the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps' (IRGC) forces, 45 were from
the ground forces of the Iranian army, 22 from the logistics
headquarters, three from the army air force units, and the
rest were family members.
</P>
<P>
The plane was en route from Dezful in southwest Iran to
the religious city of Mashhad in the northeastern province of
Khorasan and crashed when it flew almost near its destination.
</P>
<P>
The plane had lost contact with the control tower since 18:00
local time (14:30 GMT) on Thursday. The state-run Tehran Radio
reported that the C-130 plane crashed near Neyshabur.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the pilot first reported problem of the
engines and sent emergency signal SOS before the communication
was cut off.
</P>
<P>
This is the second air mishap in the past 10 days in the
country. The last air crash occurred on March 3 as a French-made
Falcon aircraft crashed 25 kilometers northest of Ardebil city in
northeastern Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Falcon pilot and three flight engineers, all members of
the Iranian army's airborne unit, died in the Ardebil
crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola Decides to Reorganize Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Council of Ministers today
decided to carry out reform in the government by adding two new
ministries, canceling one and upgrading four secretariats into
the position of ministries.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued at the end of a meeting said in
consideration of the imminent formation of the government of
national unity and reconciliation, the council of ministers
decided to set up the portfolios of science and technology, and
Posts and Telecommunications, and cancel the state secretariat of
environment.
</P>
<P>
It upgrades the secretariats of transport and communication,
energy and water, women and veterans into the ministries of
transport, women, energy and water resources as well as veterans.
</P>
<P>
Special committees would be set up to create conditions of
personnel and materials for the new ministries, the statement
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
