<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AL Chief Calls for Implementation of UN Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Esmat Abdul Meguid, Secretary
General of the Arab League (AL), reiterated here today the
necessity to implement U.N. Security Council Resolution 425, and
called on the United Nations to respect its resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Meguid, who arrived in Beirut Thursday to participate in
commemoration activities of the Israeli occupation of south
Lebanon since March 14, 1978, held meetings today with Lebanese
President Elias Hrawi, House Speaker Nabih Berri and Foreign
Minister Farez Boueiz.
</P>
<P>
At the end of his talks with the Lebanese foreign minister, the
AL chief said: "We must implement and uphold Resolution
425, and ask the United Nations and the Security Council to
respect its resolutions and implement them, just as they
implement others."
</P>
<P>
Resolution 425, adopted by the U.N. Security Council
following the Israeli invasion of Lebanon in 1978, demands an
unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think that the Israeli existence in south Lebanon
is a pleasure trip, and the Jewish state is paying a high
price," Meguid said.
</P>
<P>
"If it decided today to withdraw from this area, it would
avoid additional catastrophes and big losses," the secretary
general underlined.
</P>
<P>
He described the situation of the Middle East peace process
as "dangerous," but said that the Arab countries have "chosen
the peace as a strategic choice."
</P>
<P>
"The peace process is currently threatened, there are
dangers," Meguid said, "so we are desirous to advance in this
process, on the road to a just and comprehensive peace without
hegemony, control and without giving up our rights."
</P>
<P>
He stressed a unity of other Arab states with Lebanon, noting
that Lebanon has proved its tenacity in its resistance against
occupation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
