<HEADLINE> Chirac Asks Europeans to Take Up Responsibility </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today called on Europeans to take up responsibility for Albania
when the European Union foreign ministers meet this week in the
Netherlands, said a presidential spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
"France hopes that in liaison with its partners the Europeans
could bring their contribution to any operation which will be
decided within the framework of a political solution, the only one
to solve the crisis," she said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also hailed the good work done today by the French
troops in evacuating 88 people, including 45 French nationals,
from Albania on board five military helicopters to the Italian
port of Prindisi.
</P>
<P>
The French troops are carrying out a second rotation of
evacuation of foreigners from the Balkan state.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a French Foreign Ministry spokesman said that France
will send observers to Albania within the mission of the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
"France brings its entire support to the mission of the OSCE
led by former Austrian Chancellor Franz Vranitzky and it is ready
to contribute to the success of this initiative, including through
sending at the due moment French observers within this mission of
the OSCE," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Vranitzky today proposed the dispatch of an international
police force to Albania during his talks with Albanian Prime
Minister Bashkim Fino on an Italian warship in the Adriatic Sea.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that France remains very worried by the
situation in Albania and by its possible regional implications.
</P>
<P>
France also asked the West European Union, the military
alliance of Western European countries of which France is the
current president, to study contributions it could bring to solve
the Albania crisis, he said.
</P>
<P>
Danish Foreign Minister Niels Helveg Petersen, who is the
current president of the OSCE, said today that a military
intervention in Albania by Europe is "likely." 
</P>
</TEXT>
