efforts to bring a permanent peace to Angola, he said.
</P>
<P>
The WFP, the second largest assistance body in the United
Nations, will play a positive role in helping the African
governments develop their countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zejjar signed Thursday with the Angolan government an
understanding protocol under which the WFP will offer aid to more
than 600,000 Angolan war refugees abroad who are expected to
begin to return home from May.
</P>
