<P>
Employment growth rates are translated into office demand based
on assumptions on office occupancy rates, according to the study.
</P>
<P>
Calculations for the minimum scenario result in a projected
requirement of 10-15 million sq ft of office space in the Square
Mile over the next 10 years and an additional 5-10 million sq ft
for the five years after that.
</P>
<P>
The growth scenarios raise many questions over the location of
such activity in London and consequent implications for public
services, transport infrastructure and labor requirement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 20:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sporadic Shellings in S. Lebanon on 19th </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Sporadic shellings took place in
south Lebanon today, but a relative calm shrouded the area on the
19th anniversary of Israel's first invasion against this country
and the Israeli occupation of nearly one tenth of its territories.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said that the Israeli forces in the so-called
"security zone" in south Lebanon fired about 20 artillery shells
in the morning and afternoon at the vicinities of several south
Lebanese villages without causing casualties.
</P>
<P>
Israeli warplanes also hovered at medium and low altitude
over the areas of Natatiyeh, Iglim Al-Toffah and the Western
Beqaa.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God,
announced that they fired artilleries and heavy machine guns at
a number of Israeli positions in the buffer zone Israel
self-carved in 1985.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the Shiite fundamentalist group
said that one group of its fighters launched an attack on the
Israeli position at Sujoud this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that a number of Israeli soldiers were killed or
wounded in the bombardment and attack, but the casualties have
not been confirmed by Israel.
</P>
<P>
The pro-Syrian Amal Movement, another Muslim Shiite moderate
organization headed by Lebanese House Speaker Nabih Berri, said
that its fighters attacked a position of the Israeli-backed South
Lebanon Army militia at Zamrya in the occupied enclave.
</P>
<P>
It said that the guerrillas used mortars and rocket-propelled
grenades in the attack.
</P>
<P>
However, the security sources in south Lebanon noted that
these minor clashes did not go beyond daily frictions on the
last active battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict, which has
become a barometer of the situation in the region.
</P>
<P>
In a rally commemorating the first Israeli aggression against
Lebanon on March 14, 1978, House Speaker Berri warned of the
consequences of "Lebanon's collapse," and called on the other
Arab states to "live up to their promises."
</P>
<P>
The thorn remains as it was 18 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the rally held in the south suburb of Beirut, the
capital of Lebanon, this afternoon, Berri said, "We want the Arab
brothers to make their best taking part in the creation of a just
and comprehensive peace in the region."
</P>
<P>
He said that Lebanon should be turned into an
"Arab sample of tenacity and resistance, and Lebanon's collapse
will lead to a collapse of the Arab history and the Arab
struggle (against the Zionism) in the past 50 years."
</P>
<P>
Berri added that the making of peace in this country needed
the other Arab countries to "live up to their promises to
provide material supports for Lebanon's tenacity."
</P>
<P>
He also called for the establishment of an Arab and
international foundation for assisting Lebanon in order to make
contributions to Lebanon's reconstruction process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
