<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EAC Marks Its First Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Vice-President
Omar Ali Juma today called for strengthened economic and trade
cooperation within the one-year-old East African Cooperation
(EAC), reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Juma commended the EAC Commission Secretariat for its efforts
to form a single market in the region at the celebrations marking
the first anniversary of the EAC in Arusha, northern Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
He said the EAC facilitated the convertibility of the
currencies of Tanzania, Kenya and Uganda in the past 12 months.
</P>
<P>
The EAC also eased cross border movement of people and goods,
set up the regional business council and a regional capital and
securities markets authority in the past year.
</P>
<P>
The three EAC member states are planning to introduce an east
African passport next month, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, there was still a long way to go for the EAC, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We must take cognizance of the stark truth that this is just
the beginning of a long and arduous journey we have undertaken to
build our cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
"All of us, as East Africans, must redouble our efforts. We
are all stakeholders in this endeavor," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he called upon the EAC member states to fight
desertification which is threating the region.
</P>
<P>
"I urge the member states to treat it as a matter of high
priority and intensify our efforts before it is too late and our
region is engulfed by desert," he added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Nicholas Biwott, the Commission Chairman and the
Kenyan Minister responsible for EAC's affairs, said that in the
past 12 months eastern African people have demonstrated the need
for working together.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the importance of protecting peace and security
in the region, saying the factors were a pre-requisite for
sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's Minister of State for EAC Rebecca Kadaga also
pledged her country's continued commitment to the EAC.
</P>
<P>
She said the people in eastern Africa have supported the
commission with great enthusiasm, testifying their resolve to
restore what was lost 20 year ago.
</P>
<P>
About 400 people, including high-ranking government officials
and businessmen from Tanzania, Kenya and Uganda, attended the
celebrations.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations will last three days.
</P>
<P>
The Secretariat of the EAC Commission was launched by
presidents Benjamin Mkapa of Tanzania, Daniel Arap Moi of Kenya
and Yoweri Museveni of Uganda in Arusha on March 14, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The EAC has its roots stretching back to the days before the
defunct East African Community which collapsed in 1977. enditem

