(ACP) Chamber of Commerce will hold a meeting in Belgium next
week to discuss the establishment of a full-time secretariat to
look into future plans after the Lome IV Convention expires in
2000.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Zimbabwe News Agency, President of
the ACP Chamber of Commerce Danny Meyer said today they will meet
officials of various European Union departments, the EU
Commission and the ACP Secretariat.
