<HEADLINE> New National Bank to Replace Old One in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A new national bank named the
Camerounian International Deposit and Credit Bank (BICEC) is to
open next week in Cameroun..
</P>
<P>
The creation of the BICEC aims to replace a bank called the
Camerounian International Industrial and Commercial Bank (BICIC),
said a communique of the minister of state of Cameroun in charge
of economy and finance today.
</P>
<P>
All the shares and savings of customers of the BICIC will be
taken over by the new bank in order to facilitate an easy
transfer of operations from the BICIC to the BICEC, said the
communique.
</P>
<P>
The minister ordered the closure of the BICIC until 1:00 p.m.
of March 19 then the customers can turn up for normal banking
operations with the new institution.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique, the measure adopted by the
monetary authorities is in line with the restructuring of the
banking sector in Cameroun. enditem

