<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scientists Create World Water, Climate Database </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The World Water and Climate
Atlas for Agriculture, a global computer database about
precipitation and temperatures, will be released Sunday night, an
agricultural consultative group announced today.
</P>
<P>
The database, created by scientists at the International
Irrigation Management Institute (IIMI) and Utah State University,
will serve as a high-tech tool for farmers, agronomists,
meteorologists and government policy makers, IIMI researchers say.
</P>
<P>
"The Atlas integrates the available agricultural climate data
into one computer program and represents the most comprehensive,
quality-controlled climatic data set in existence," says Ismail
Serageldin, Vice President for Environmentally Sustainable
Development of the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
Created from data received from 56,000 weather stations around
the world, the Atlas covers the 1961 to 1990 period. "It will
assume even greater importance in coming years, as water becomes
scarcer," says David Seckler of IIMI at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
The Atlas enables users to zoom in on any 2.5 square kilometers
region of the globe and extract data such as precipitation and
probability of precipitation, maximum and minimum temperatures and
average temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Using this meteorological map, engineers can develop specific
plans for irrigation and water conservation projects; farmers can
assess the potential for plant adaptation to climatic conditions;
and scientists can combine the data with crop growth models to
select and breed different plants.
</P>
<P>
Some of the data is now available on CD-ROM and the entire
Atlas will be accessible on the Internet in July. "The next
version of the Atlas will improve the precision by more than 50
percent, presenting the data at one kilometer intervals" when new
or improved data available, especially from local stations, Mr.
Seckler added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970315.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
